## In open source, which is important, liberalism or democracy?
When utilizing generative AI, we are considering using the open source code as one way to check whether it is related to copyright or patents.
Open source allows a large number of people to see it and take the time to verify who owns the rights.
If you want to auto-generate source code, it is preferable to have output based on open source.
By the way, is democracy important in the open source world? Or is liberalism important? In the spirit of C, programmers should not be prevented from doing what they intend to do.
The answers are by ChatGPT

